{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":888,"text":"Thirteen trillion dollars in wealth"},{"time":3000,"text":"has evaporated over the course\nof the last two years."},{"time":6553,"text":"We've questioned the future of capitalism."},{"time":8874,"text":"We've questioned the financial industry."},{"time":11250,"text":"We've looked at our government oversight."},{"time":13250,"text":"We've questioned where we're going."},{"time":14968,"text":"And yet, at the same time,"},{"time":16301,"text":"this very well may be\na seminal moment in American history,"},{"time":19201,"text":"an opportunity for the consumer\nto actually take control and guide us"},{"time":23550,"text":"to a new trajectory in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25750,"text":"I'm calling this The Great Unwind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27499,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":28525,"text":"And the idea is a simple, simple idea,"},{"time":31150,"text":"which is the fact that the consumer\nhas moved from a state of anxiety"},{"time":35254,"text":"to action."},{"time":36436,"text":"Consumers who represent 72 percent\nof the GDP of America"},{"time":40699,"text":"have actually started, just like banks\nand just like businesses,"},{"time":44167,"text":"to de-leverage, to unwind\ntheir leverage in daily life,"},{"time":48275,"text":"to remove themselves\nfrom the liability and risk"},{"time":51250,"text":"that presents itself as they move forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54150,"text":"So, to understand this --\nand I'm going to stress this --"},{"time":56907,"text":"it's not about the consumer\nbeing in retreat."},{"time":59094,"text":"The consumer is empowered."},{"time":60478,"text":"To understand this, we'll step back\nand look at what's happened"},{"time":63759,"text":"over the last year and a half."},{"time":65678,"text":"So if you've been gone,\nthis is the CliffsNotes"},{"time":67921,"text":"on what's happened in the economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69569,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70597,"text":"Unemployment up. Housing values down.\nEquity markets down."},{"time":73691,"text":"Commodity prices are like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75321,"text":"If you're a mom trying to manage a budget,"},{"time":77593,"text":"and oil was 150 dollars\na barrel last summer,"},{"time":80282,"text":"and it's somewhere between 50 and 70,"},{"time":82079,"text":"do you plan vacations?"},{"time":83266,"text":"How do you buy?"},{"time":84448,"text":"What's your strategy in your household?\nWill the bailout work?"},{"time":87392,"text":"We have national debt, Detroit,\ncurrency valuations, health care --"},{"time":90591,"text":"all these issues facing us."},{"time":91912,"text":"You put them all together,\nmix them up in a bouillabaisse,"},{"time":94662,"text":"and you have consumer confidence\nthat's basically a ticking time bomb."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98017,"text":"In fact, let's go back and look\nat what caused this crisis,"},{"time":101018,"text":"because the consumer,\nall of us, in our daily lives,"},{"time":103520,"text":"actually contributed\na large part to the problem."},{"time":106020,"text":"This is something I call\nthe 50-20 paradox."},{"time":108824,"text":"It took us 50 years"},{"time":111600,"text":"to reach annual savings ratings\nof almost 10 percent."},{"time":115380,"text":"Fifty years."},{"time":116600,"text":"Do you know what this was right here?\nThis was World War II."},{"time":119502,"text":"Do you know why savings was so high?"},{"time":121340,"text":"There was nothing to buy,\nunless you wanted to buy some rivets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124674,"text":"What happened, though,\nover the course of the last 20 years,"},{"time":127628,"text":"we went from a 10 percent savings rate\nto a negative savings rate."},{"time":131812,"text":"Because we binged."},{"time":133489,"text":"We bought extra-large cars,\nsupersized everything,"},{"time":137306,"text":"we bought remedies\nfor restless leg syndrome."},{"time":140038,"text":"All these things together\nbasically created a factor"},{"time":143968,"text":"where the consumer drove us\nheadlong into the crisis"},{"time":146580,"text":"that we face today."},{"time":147877,"text":"The personal debt-to-income ratio\nbasically went from 65 to 135 percent"},{"time":154178,"text":"in the span of about 15 years."},{"time":156710,"text":"So consumers got over-leveraged."},{"time":158821,"text":"And of course our banks did as well,\nas did our federal government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162026,"text":"This is an absolutely staggering chart."},{"time":164116,"text":"It shows leverage,\ntrended out from 1919 to 2009."},{"time":168747,"text":"And what you end up seeing\nis the whole phenomenon"},{"time":171423,"text":"that we are actually stepping forth\nand basically leveraging"},{"time":175303,"text":"future education, future children\nin our households."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178506,"text":"So if you look at this in the context\nof visualizing the bailout,"},{"time":181630,"text":"what you can see is,\nif you stack up dollar bills,"},{"time":184150,"text":"first of all, 360,000 dollars"},{"time":186416,"text":"is about the size of a five-foot-four guy."},{"time":188959,"text":"But if you stack it up, you see\nthis amazing, staggering amount of dollars"},{"time":193260,"text":"that have been put into the system\nto fund and bail us out."},{"time":196150,"text":"So this is the first 315 billion."},{"time":198339,"text":"But I read this fact the other day,"},{"time":200136,"text":"that one trillion seconds\nequals 32,000 years."},{"time":203470,"text":"So if you think about that,"},{"time":204811,"text":"the context, the casualness\nwith which we talk about"},{"time":207331,"text":"trillion-dollar bailout here\nand trillion there,"},{"time":209608,"text":"we are stacking ourselves up\nfor long-term leverage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213017,"text":"However, consumers have moved."},{"time":215693,"text":"They are taking responsibility."},{"time":217756,"text":"What we're seeing\nis an uptake in the savings rate."},{"time":220309,"text":"In fact, 11 straight months\nof savings have happened"},{"time":223048,"text":"since the beginning of the crisis."},{"time":224719,"text":"We're working our way back up\nto that 10 percent."},{"time":227107,"text":"Also, remarkably, in the fourth quarter,"},{"time":229061,"text":"spending dropped\nto its lowest level in 62 years --"},{"time":232466,"text":"almost a 3.7 percent decline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235150,"text":"Visa now reports that more people\nare using debit cards than credit cards."},{"time":239054,"text":"So we're starting to pay for things\nwith money that we have."},{"time":242471,"text":"And we're starting to be much more careful\nabout how we save and invest."},{"time":246150,"text":"But that's not really the whole story,"},{"time":248150,"text":"because this has also been a dramatic\ntime of transformation."},{"time":251091,"text":"And you've got to admit,\nover the last year and a half,"},{"time":253741,"text":"consumers have been doing\nsome weird things."},{"time":255833,"text":"It's pretty staggering,\nwhat we've lived through."},{"time":258148,"text":"If you take into account\nthat 80 percent of all Americans"},{"time":260868,"text":"were born after World War II,"},{"time":262288,"text":"this was essentially our Depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264045,"text":"And so, as a result,\nsome crazy things have happened."},{"time":266874,"text":"I'll give you some examples."},{"time":268248,"text":"Let's talk about dentists, vasectomies,\nguns and shark attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272937,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274749,"text":"Dentists report molars --\npeople grinding their teeth,"},{"time":278656,"text":"coming in and reporting\nthat they've had stress."},{"time":281043,"text":"So there's an increase in people\nhaving to have their fillings replaced."},{"time":284489,"text":"Gun sales, according to the FBI,\nwho does background checks,"},{"time":287807,"text":"are up almost 25 percent since January."},{"time":290925,"text":"Vasectomies are up 48 percent,\naccording to the Cornell Institute."},{"time":295602,"text":"And lastly, but a very good point,"},{"time":298030,"text":"hopefully not related\nto the former point I just made,"},{"time":300630,"text":"which is that shark attacks\nare at their lowest level from 2003."},{"time":304117,"text":"Does anybody know why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306011,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307217,"text":"No one's at the beach."},{"time":308409,"text":"So there's a bright side to everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310329,"text":"But seriously, what we see happening,"},{"time":312539,"text":"and the reason I want to stress\nthat the consumer is not in retreat,"},{"time":315824,"text":"is that this is a tremendous opportunity"},{"time":317863,"text":"for the consumer who drove us\ninto this recession"},{"time":320481,"text":"to lead us right back out."},{"time":322030,"text":"What I mean by that is we can\nmove from mindless consumption"},{"time":325396,"text":"to mindful consumption."},{"time":327448,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328632,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329731,"text":"If you think about the last three decades,"},{"time":331787,"text":"the consumer has moved\nfrom savvy about marketing in the '90s,"},{"time":335093,"text":"to gathering all these amazing social\nand search tools in this decade."},{"time":339094,"text":"But the one thing holding them back\nis the ability to discriminate."},{"time":342447,"text":"By restricting their demand,"},{"time":343808,"text":"consumers can actually align\ntheir values with their spending,"},{"time":347150,"text":"and drive capitalism and business\nto not just be about more,"},{"time":350754,"text":"but to be about better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351944,"text":"We're going to explain that right now."},{"time":353945,"text":"Based on Y&amp;R's BrandAsset Valuator,"},{"time":356750,"text":"proprietary tool of VML\nand Young &amp; Rubicam,"},{"time":359475,"text":"we set out to understand\nwhat's been happening in the crisis"},{"time":362383,"text":"with the consumer marketplace."},{"time":363948,"text":"We found a couple\nof really interesting things."},{"time":366189,"text":"We're going to go\nthrough four value shifts"},{"time":368640,"text":"that we see driving\nnew consumer behaviors,"},{"time":371000,"text":"that offer new management principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373081,"text":"The first cultural value shift we see"},{"time":374915,"text":"is this tendency toward something\nwe call \"liquid life.\""},{"time":377565,"text":"This is the movement"},{"time":378739,"text":"from Americans defining\ntheir success on having things"},{"time":381844,"text":"to having liquidity,"},{"time":383150,"text":"because the less excess\nthat you have around you,"},{"time":385866,"text":"the more nimble and fleet of foot you are."},{"time":388042,"text":"As a result, déclassé consumption is in."},{"time":390536,"text":"Déclassé consumption is the whole idea\nthat spending money frivolously"},{"time":394495,"text":"makes you look a little bit anti-fashion."},{"time":397257,"text":"The management principle\nis dollars and cents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399770,"text":"So let's look at some examples\nof this déclassé consumption"},{"time":402638,"text":"that falls out of this value."},{"time":404090,"text":"The first thing is,\nsomething must be happening"},{"time":406411,"text":"when P. Diddy vows to tone down his bling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408511,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409549,"text":"But seriously, we also have\nthis phenomenon"},{"time":411915,"text":"on Madison Avenue and in other places,"},{"time":413864,"text":"where people are actually\nwalking out of luxury boutiques"},{"time":416811,"text":"with ordinary, generic paper bags\nto hide the brand purchases."},{"time":420648,"text":"We see high-end haggling in fashion today,"},{"time":423649,"text":"high-end haggling\nfor luxury and real estate."},{"time":426150,"text":"We also see just a relaxing of ego,"},{"time":428546,"text":"and sort of a dismantling of artifice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430822,"text":"This is a story on the yacht club\nthat's all basically blue collar."},{"time":434693,"text":"Blue-collar yacht club --\nwhere you can join,"},{"time":436891,"text":"but you've got to work in the boatyard\nas condition of membership."},{"time":440150,"text":"We also see the trend toward tourism\nthat's a little bit more low-key:"},{"time":444835,"text":"agritourism -- going to vineyards\nand going to farms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447986,"text":"And then we also see this movement\nforward from dollars and cents."},{"time":451635,"text":"What businesses can do to connect\nwith these new mindsets"},{"time":454374,"text":"is really interesting."},{"time":455565,"text":"A couple things that are kind of cool."},{"time":457434,"text":"One is that Frito-Lay figured out\nthis liquidity thing with their consumer."},{"time":461151,"text":"They found their consumer had more\nmoney at the beginning of the month,"},{"time":464578,"text":"less at the end of the month."},{"time":466011,"text":"So they started to change their packaging:"},{"time":468048,"text":"larger packs at the beginning\nof the month,"},{"time":470094,"text":"smaller packaging at the end of the month."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472138,"text":"Really interestingly, too,\nwas the San Francisco Giants."},{"time":474881,"text":"They've just instituted dynamic pricing."},{"time":477150,"text":"It takes into account everything\nfrom the pitcher match-ups,"},{"time":480393,"text":"to the weather, to the team records,"},{"time":482260,"text":"in setting prices for the consumer."},{"time":484688,"text":"Another quick example of these types\nof movements is the rise of Zynga."},{"time":489743,"text":"Zynga has risen on the consumer's desire"},{"time":492047,"text":"to not want to be locked in to fixed cost."},{"time":494083,"text":"Again, this theme is about variable\ncost, variable living."},{"time":496867,"text":"So micro-payments have become huge."},{"time":498763,"text":"And lastly, some people are using Hulu"},{"time":501366,"text":"as a device to get rid\nof their cable bill."},{"time":503462,"text":"So, really clever ideas there\nthat are being taken ahold of"},{"time":507076,"text":"and that marketers\nare starting to understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509271,"text":"The second of the four values\nis this movement toward"},{"time":511925,"text":"ethics and fair play."},{"time":513254,"text":"We see that play itself out\nwith empathy and respect."},{"time":516415,"text":"The consumer is demanding it."},{"time":518060,"text":"And, as a result, businesses\nmust provide not only value,"},{"time":521250,"text":"but values."},{"time":522426,"text":"Increasingly, consumers are looking\nat the culture of the company,"},{"time":525623,"text":"at their conduct in the marketplace."},{"time":527392,"text":"So we see with empathy and respect"},{"time":529084,"text":"lots of really hopeful things\ncome out of this recession."},{"time":531904,"text":"I'll give you a few examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533319,"text":"One is the rise toward communities\nand neighborhoods,"},{"time":535868,"text":"and increased emphasis on your neighbors\nas your support system."},{"time":539606,"text":"Also, a wonderful by-product\nof a really lousy thing,"},{"time":543677,"text":"which has been unemployment,"},{"time":545069,"text":"is a rise in volunteerism\nthat's been noted in our country."},{"time":547894,"text":"We also see the phenomenon --\nsome of you may have \"boomerang kids\" --"},{"time":551588,"text":"these are \"boomerang alumni,\""},{"time":553249,"text":"where universities are actually\nreconnecting with alumni"},{"time":556006,"text":"and helping them with jobs,\nsharing skills and retraining."},{"time":558811,"text":"We also talked about character\nand professionalism."},{"time":561383,"text":"We had this miracle on the Hudson\nin New York City in January,"},{"time":565150,"text":"and suddenly Sully has become\na key name on BabyCenter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569150,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570244,"text":"So, from a value and values standpoint,"},{"time":572664,"text":"what companies can do is connect\nin lots of different ways."},{"time":575641,"text":"Microsoft is doing something wonderful."},{"time":577557,"text":"They are actually vowing to retrain\ntwo million Americans with IT training,"},{"time":581419,"text":"using their existing infrastructure\nto do something good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584545,"text":"Also, a really interesting\ncompany is GORE-TEX."},{"time":587030,"text":"GORE-TEX is all about\npersonal accountability"},{"time":589764,"text":"of their management and their employees,"},{"time":591737,"text":"to the point where they really\nkind of shun the idea of bosses."},{"time":595319,"text":"But they also talk about the fact\nthat their executives --"},{"time":598108,"text":"all of their expense reports\nare put onto their company intranet"},{"time":601204,"text":"for everyone to see."},{"time":602407,"text":"Complete transparency."},{"time":604150,"text":"Think twice before you have\nthat bottle of wine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606450,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":607531,"text":"The third of the four laws\nof post-crisis consumerism"},{"time":610328,"text":"is about durable living."},{"time":611837,"text":"We're seeing in our data\nthat consumers are realizing"},{"time":614398,"text":"this is a marathon, not a sprint."},{"time":616150,"text":"They're digging in and looking\nfor ways to extract value"},{"time":619033,"text":"out of every purchase they make."},{"time":621150,"text":"Witness the fact that Americans\nare holding on to their cars"},{"time":624089,"text":"longer than ever before:\n9.4 years on average, in March."},{"time":627975,"text":"A record."},{"time":629150,"text":"We also see the fact that libraries\nhave become a huge resource for America."},{"time":633150,"text":"Did you know that 68 percent\nof Americans now carry a library card?"},{"time":637016,"text":"The highest percentage ever\nin our nation's history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639505,"text":"So what you see in this trend\nis also the accumulation of knowledge."},{"time":643150,"text":"Continuing education is up."},{"time":644893,"text":"Everything is focused\non betterment, training,"},{"time":647555,"text":"development and moving forward."},{"time":649364,"text":"We also see a big DIY movement."},{"time":652424,"text":"I was fascinated to learn that 30 percent\nof all homes in America"},{"time":656612,"text":"are actually built by owners."},{"time":658150,"text":"That includes cottages and the like,"},{"time":660032,"text":"but 30 percent."},{"time":661224,"text":"People are getting their hands dirty,\nrolling up their sleeves."},{"time":664260,"text":"They want these skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665451,"text":"We see it with the phenomenon of raising\nbackyard hens, chickens and ducks."},{"time":669039,"text":"And when you work out the math,\nthey say it doesn't work,"},{"time":671751,"text":"but the principle is there;"},{"time":673075,"text":"it's about being sustainable\nand taking care of yourself."},{"time":675814,"text":"Then we look at the High Line\nin New York City,"},{"time":678449,"text":"an excellent use of reimagining\nexisting infrastructure"},{"time":681241,"text":"for something good,"},{"time":682424,"text":"which is a brand-new park\nin New York City."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684483,"text":"So what brands can do, and companies,\nis pay dividends to consumers,"},{"time":688598,"text":"be a brand that lasts,"},{"time":690150,"text":"offer transparency,"},{"time":691563,"text":"promise you're going to be there\nbeyond today's sale."},{"time":694081,"text":"Perfect example of that is Patagonia."},{"time":696150,"text":"Patagonia's \"Footprint Chronicles\""},{"time":697888,"text":"basically goes through and tracks\nevery product they make,"},{"time":701710,"text":"and gives you social responsibility,"},{"time":703524,"text":"and helps you understand the ethics\nbehind the product they make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707087,"text":"Another great example is Fidelity."},{"time":708893,"text":"Rather than instant cash-back rewards\non your credit or debit purchases,"},{"time":712603,"text":"this is about 529 rewards\nfor your student education."},{"time":717523,"text":"Or the interesting company Sunrun."},{"time":719634,"text":"I love this company."},{"time":720813,"text":"They've created a consumer collective"},{"time":722904,"text":"where they put solar panels on households"},{"time":725274,"text":"and create a consumer-based utility,"},{"time":727393,"text":"where the electricity they generate"},{"time":729115,"text":"is basically pumped back out\ninto the marketplace."},{"time":731763,"text":"So it's a consumer-driven co-op."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733523,"text":"The fourth post-crisis\nconsumerism that we see"},{"time":737221,"text":"is this movement\nabout \"return to the fold.\""},{"time":739562,"text":"It's incredibly important right now."},{"time":741385,"text":"Trust is not parceled out, as we all know."},{"time":743993,"text":"It's now about connecting\nto your communities,"},{"time":746209,"text":"connecting to your social networks."},{"time":747995,"text":"In my book, I talked about the fact"},{"time":749733,"text":"that 72 percent of people trust\nwhat other people say"},{"time":752432,"text":"about a brand or a company,"},{"time":753907,"text":"versus 15 percent on advertising."},{"time":755973,"text":"So in that respect, cooperative\nconsumerism has really taken off."},{"time":759717,"text":"This is about consumers working\ntogether to get what they want"},{"time":762724,"text":"out of the marketplace."},{"time":763924,"text":"Let's look at a couple of quick examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765925,"text":"The artisanal movement is huge:"},{"time":767522,"text":"everything about locally\nderived products and services,"},{"time":770603,"text":"supporting your local neighborhoods,"},{"time":772411,"text":"whether it's cheeses,\nwines and other products."},{"time":775411,"text":"Also this rise of local currencies."},{"time":778093,"text":"Realizing that it's difficult\nto get loans in this environment,"},{"time":781092,"text":"you're doing business\nwith people you trust"},{"time":783175,"text":"in your local markets."},{"time":784378,"text":"So this rise of local currency\nis another really interesting phenomenon."},{"time":788270,"text":"And then they did a recent report\nI thought was fascinating."},{"time":791916,"text":"They actually started, in certain\ncommunities in the United States,"},{"time":795113,"text":"to publish people's electricity usage."},{"time":797164,"text":"And what they found out is when\nthat was available for public record,"},{"time":800499,"text":"the people's electricity usage\nin those communities dropped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804511,"text":"Then we also look\nat the idea of cow-pooling,"},{"time":807150,"text":"which is the whole phenomenon\nof consumers organizing together"},{"time":811369,"text":"to buy meat from organic farms,\nthat they know is safe and controlled"},{"time":815286,"text":"in the way that they want it\nto be controlled."},{"time":817496,"text":"And then there's this other really\ninteresting movement in California,"},{"time":821087,"text":"which is about carrot mobs."},{"time":822594,"text":"The traditional thing would be\nto boycott, right? Have a stick."},{"time":825664,"text":"Well, why not have a carrot?"},{"time":827034,"text":"So these are consumers organizing,\npooling their resources"},{"time":830362,"text":"to incentify companies to do good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833150,"text":"And then we look at what companies can do."},{"time":835971,"text":"This is all the opportunity\nabout being a community organizer."},{"time":839448,"text":"You have to realize\nthat you can't fight and control this."},{"time":842439,"text":"You actually need to organize it."},{"time":844073,"text":"You need to harness it.\nYou need to give it meaning."},{"time":846622,"text":"And there's lots of really\ninteresting examples here."},{"time":849858,"text":"First is just the rise of the fact\nthat Zagat's has actually moved out of"},{"time":854675,"text":"and diversified from rating restaurants,"},{"time":856927,"text":"into actually rating health care."},{"time":859150,"text":"So what credentials does Zagat's have?"},{"time":861303,"text":"Well, they have a lot,"},{"time":862497,"text":"because it's their network of people."},{"time":864365,"text":"So that becomes\na very powerful force for them"},{"time":866932,"text":"to make their brand more elastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869150,"text":"Then you look at the phenomenon of Kogi."},{"time":871936,"text":"This Kogi doesn't exist.\nIt's a moving truck."},{"time":874937,"text":"It's a moving truck through L.A.,"},{"time":876560,"text":"and the only way you can find it\nis through Twitter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":880161,"text":"Or you look at"},{"time":881338,"text":"Johnson &amp; Johnson's \"Momversations,\"\na phenomenal blog that's been built up,"},{"time":886424,"text":"where J&amp;J basically is tapping\ninto the power of mommy bloggers,"},{"time":890578,"text":"allowing them to create a forum\nwhere they can communicate and connect."},{"time":895050,"text":"And it's also become a very valuable\nadvertising revenue for J&amp;J as well."},{"time":899913,"text":"This, plus the fact that you've got\nphenomenal work from CEOs,"},{"time":904151,"text":"from Ford to Zappos,\nconnecting on Twitter,"},{"time":906715,"text":"creating an open environment,"},{"time":908150,"text":"allowing their employees\nto be part of the process,"},{"time":911212,"text":"rather than hidden behind walls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":912944,"text":"You see this rising force\nin total transparency and openness"},{"time":917173,"text":"that companies are starting to adopt,"},{"time":918985,"text":"all because the consumer is demanding it."},{"time":921316,"text":"So when we look at this and step back,"},{"time":923286,"text":"what I believe is that the crisis\nthat exists today is definitely real."},{"time":927502,"text":"It's been tremendously\npowerful for consumers."},{"time":930150,"text":"But at the same time,\nthis is also a tremendous opportunity."},{"time":933737,"text":"The Chinese character for crisis\nis actually the same side"},{"time":937228,"text":"of the same coin."},{"time":938419,"text":"Crisis equals opportunity."},{"time":940150,"text":"What we're seeing with consumers\nright now is the ability for them"},{"time":943668,"text":"to actually lead us forward\nout of this recession."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946328,"text":"So we believe that values-driven spending\nwill force capitalism to be better:"},{"time":951150,"text":"it will drive innovation;"},{"time":953054,"text":"it will make longer-lasting products;"},{"time":955179,"text":"it will create better,\nmore intuitive customer service;"},{"time":957799,"text":"and it will give us the opportunity\nto connect with companies"},{"time":960700,"text":"that share the values that we share."},{"time":962795,"text":"So when we look back and step out at this"},{"time":964838,"text":"and see the beginning of these trends\nthat we're seeing in our data,"},{"time":968150,"text":"we see a very hopeful picture\nfor the future of America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971023,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972215,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}